'''''Star Wars Insider'' 33''' is the thirty-third issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in Spring [[1997]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by Dan Madsen with [[Rick McCallum]]}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe John Hollis]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*"[[The Wonder Column|The New Wonder Column]]" {{C|by [[Anthony Daniels]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" {{C|by [[Bob Cooper]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Star Wars World Premiere|''Star Wars'' World Premiere]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Finally, after 20 years, ''Star Wars'' gets the gala opening it deserves. [[Scott Chernoff]] and the ''Insider'' were there.</small>
*"[[Wampa Attack!]]" {{C|by [[Athena Yvette Portillo|Athena Portillo]]}}
*:<small>Athena Portillo digs deep into the snow to discover the secrets of the ice creature.</small>
*"[[An Insider interview with Phil Tippett|An ''Insider'' interview with Phil Tippett]]" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*:<small>[[Jamie Painter]] finds that the former [[Industrial Light & Magic|ILM]]-er who made the [[Tauntaun/Legends|Tauntauns]] trot and the [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|AT-ATs]] walk is busier than ever.</small>
*"[[It's Cold Outside! The First Star Wars Customizable Card Game World Tournament|It's Cold Outside! The First ''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game World Tournament]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>What happens when [[Decipher]] invites the best ''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game players in the world to duke it out? [[Jon Bradley Snyder]] reports.</small>
*"[[Meco and Other Galactic Funk]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff & Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*:<small>What's the man who made ''Star Wars'' disco up to these days? The ''Insider'' gets down with Meco Monardo.</small>

